  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> brown&nbsp;onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Deseed the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>beef mince </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>beef</strong> to kitchen paper and return the pan to a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and <strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5 min or until beginning to soften</p>\r\n<p>Tip: add a little more oil if your pan is looking dry!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong> &nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and pepper have softened, return the <strong>browned beef</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped basil</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong> and <span class=\"text-highlight\">half of the</span><strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> (save the rest for later!)&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10 min or until thickened to a chilli-like consistency&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1057_step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, divide the<strong> filling</strong> between the <strong>tortillas</strong> and top them with&nbsp;half of the<strong>&nbsp;cheese</strong> (save some for the topping!)</p>\r\n<p>Roll each <strong>tortilla</strong>&nbsp;up and arrange them into an oven-proof dish&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Spoon over the remaining <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and top with the <strong>remaining cheese&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the dish in the oven for 15 min or until the cheese is golden and melted</p>",
